cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) because it deals with parsing and dependency relations in natural language. It could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) because it uses statistical models to improve parse accuracy. Additionally, it could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) because it deals with natural language understanding, Information Retrieval (cs.IR) because it involves parsing and analyzing text data, and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) because it involves finding the minimal set of fragments for maximal parse accuracy.
